com.nokia.maps.map

Class MapUrlProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nokia.maps.map.MapProvider
      • com.nokia.maps.map.MapUrlProvider

  • public abstract class MapUrlProvider
extends MapProvider
    This class offers an abstract base class for downloading map tile Images. It implements the logic for fetching tile Images from a provider's server.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public final byte[] get(int zoom,
         int column,
         int row)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.InterruptedException
        This method retrieves a byte stream of data from an online map provider. It is an implementation of the MapProvider.get(int zoom, int column, int row) method. This method is a synchronous call that may be used to obtain the necessary data that can be used to generate an Image for a given tile.
        Specified by:
        get in class MapProvider
        Parameters:
        zoom - zoom level of requested tile image
        column - column number of requested tile image
        row - row number of requested tile image
        Returns:
        A byte array representing the stream data that is passed to MapProvider.decode(byte[]) in order to obtain an Image.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - on IO errors
        java.lang.InterruptedException - when cancelled.
        See Also:
        MapProvider

      • getMimeType

        public java.lang.String getMimeType()
        This method retrieves the option mime type to be set in the HTTP connection header. The default mime type for URL overlays is PNG.
        Returns:
        MimeType if needed, null otherwise.
